theorem closure_interior_closure_interior_eq {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    closure (interior (closure (interior A))) = closure (interior A) := by
  -- First inclusion: `⊆`.
  have h₁ :
      closure (interior (closure (interior A))) ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
    have : (interior (closure (interior A)) : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) :=
      interior_subset
    exact closure_mono this
  -- Second inclusion: `⊇`, using `P1` for `closure (interior A)`.
  have hP1 : Topology.P1 (closure (interior A)) :=
    Topology.closure_interior_has_P1 (X := X) (A := A)
  have h₂ :
      (closure (interior A) : Set X) ⊆
        closure (interior (closure (interior A))) := by
    dsimp [Topology.P1] at hP1
    exact hP1
  exact subset_antisymm h₁ h₂

theorem closure_interior_closure_subset_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
  -- `interior (closure A)` is contained in `closure A`.
  have h : interior (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) :=
    interior_subset
  -- Taking closures preserves the inclusion.
  exact closure_mono h

theorem P1_implies_P1_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 A → Topology.P1 (closure A) := by
  intro hP1
  dsimp [Topology.P1] at hP1 ⊢
  -- From `A ⊆ closure (interior A)` we get `closure A ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
  have h₁ : closure A ⊆ closure (interior A) := closure_mono hP1
  -- Since `A ⊆ closure A`, we have `interior A ⊆ interior (closure A)`.
  -- Taking closures yields `closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A))`.
  have h₂ : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
    have hInt : interior A ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
      interior_mono (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure A)
    exact closure_mono hInt
  exact h₁.trans h₂

theorem P3_and_isClosed_iff_clopen {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    (Topology.P3 A ∧ IsClosed (A : Set X)) ↔
      (IsOpen (A : Set X) ∧ IsClosed (A : Set X)) := by
  constructor
  · rintro ⟨hP3, hClosed⟩
    have hOpen : IsOpen (A : Set X) :=
      ((Topology.P3_iff_isOpen_of_isClosed (X := X) (A := A) hClosed).1) hP3
    exact ⟨hOpen, hClosed⟩
  · rintro ⟨hOpen, hClosed⟩
    have hP3 : Topology.P3 A :=
      ((Topology.P3_iff_isOpen_of_isClosed (X := X) (A := A) hClosed).2) hOpen
    exact ⟨hP3, hClosed⟩
